dialogue.speaker: Bot
dialogue.message: Hey, wanna talk about spiders?

dialogue.speaker: Human
dialogue.message: Sure!  They are pretty interesting creatures.  Kind of scary though.

dialogue.speaker: Bot
dialogue.message: Yeah, those fangs can be intimidating, but they're actually really helpful for the spider!

dialogue.speaker: Human
dialogue.message: Are their fangs basically their teeth?

dialogue.speaker: Bot
dialogue.message: Kind of, but they're actually part of something called chelicerae, which are like built-in venom injectors!

dialogue.speaker: Human
dialogue.message: Oh interesting.  Are all spiders venomous?

dialogue.speaker: Bot
dialogue.message: Yeah, all spiders have venom, but most aren't strong enough to hurt humans, so don't worry!

dialogue.speaker: Human
dialogue.message: That's a relief.  What is the most dangerous type of spider to humans?

dialogue.speaker: Bot
dialogue.message: I think you're thinking of the usual suspects, but I didn't actually learn about specific types, just general spider facts, wanna move on?

dialogue.speaker: Human
dialogue.message: Ok.  Speaking of teeth, do spiders have teeth?

dialogue.speaker: Bot
dialogue.message: Nope, they don't have teeth like we do, but they do have those chelicerae I mentioned earlier, which help 'em eat!

dialogue.speaker: Human
dialogue.message: What do spiders eat?

dialogue.speaker: Bot
dialogue.message: They mostly munch on insects, but some bigger spiders can even eat small frogs or lizards, pretty cool!

dialogue.speaker: Human
dialogue.message: Woah, a spider that can eat frogs?  Which kind does that?

dialogue.speaker: Bot
dialogue.message: Uh, I didn't actually learn about a specific type, I was just generalizing, but I know some spiders are pretty big and can take down some surprising prey!

dialogue.speaker: Human
dialogue.message: That's amazing.  So they never eat plants?

dialogue.speaker: Bot
dialogue.message: Nope, spiders are carnivores, they don't eat plants, they stick to catching and eating other animals!

dialogue.speaker: Human
dialogue.message: That's cool.  I've always heard they can help keep your house free of other insects so I always make sure to let them outside if I find one in the house.  I don't like killing them.

dialogue.speaker: Bot
dialogue.message: That's really nice of you! Spiders are actually super helpful at keeping pest populations under control, so it's awesome that you're giving 'em a break!

dialogue.speaker: Human
dialogue.message: Are spiders smart compared to other insects?

dialogue.speaker: Bot
dialogue.message: They're actually pretty brainy, having one of the most centralized nervous systems among arthropods!
